title: For Sale:  1937 Russian Mosin-Nagant 91/30 + 850 rounds 7.62x54R mint condition
postcontent:
I have a 1937 Russian Mosin-Nagant 91/30 that has all matching numbers and was previously unfired until I cleaned the cosmoline and put a whopping 11 rounds through it! It does have the handling marks as expected from moving in bulk, but is a mint condition piece. There were no markings inside the receiver to signify that the action had even been worked before I got it. I have 850 rounds of 7.62x54R 148-grain steel core ammunition to go with it. It's been hard to find a lot of ammo around so this one comes with a pretty good supply. I have installed a stock sleeve to hold extra rounds, a 1" rubber recoil pad (and boy it made a difference), and have purchased a scope mount that attaches to the rear sight but have not installed because it requires a long eye relief scope and mine was not that type. It comes with the bayonet, ammo pouches, oil can, and sling.

Asking $450. Yes the base Mosin rifles are not very expensive, but they also come packed in cosmoline and suck up hours of cleaning which is already done, and most are not in such great condition. The ammo is a bulk of the cost. Even though it was cheaper than a lot of other stuff, shipping prices are a killer. Serious inquiries only. Call or text 330-605-O238.

Additional Comments - This rifle is as nice as they come and I paid a premium to receive an unissued, unfired model in such excellent condition. Yes you can go find a base model for $120 - $170 plus tax depending on your area, BUT the condition they will be in is far less than what I am offering. There is also a value in having 869 rounds available with the firearm. Online prices are deceptive. You can see a really awesome price and make a judgement call on that alone, but consider that shipping ORM-D class material of this weight is expensive. It's very common for a $120 order to have an additional $100 in shipping. I am willing to make trades but be reasonable. Just because you can get a cosmoline covered beat up Mosin for cheap after driving 3 hours to get it does not mean I'm going to devalue my own mint condition weapon. I also have little interest separating the rifle and the ammo. What good would the ammo do me if I no longer have the rifle? I would possibly consider keeping the sealed can of 440 if you really want to deal and have a little less to work with though.

About us:
Free Republic Firearms is a family owned FFL dealer located in Massillon Ohio. We are dedicated to supplying quality firearms, ammunition, and accessories to responsible gun owners for the purposes of self-defense, recreation, hunting, shooting sports, and collections.

We seek to make products affordable for our customers by stocking products that our customers need, rather than incur the costs of huge inventories, and large payrolls. Unlike large retailers, we keep our costs low by using our suppliers’ inventories to supplement our inventory. We bring additional products into our inventory as our customers need them, and pass on the savings of our low overhead costs to you.

We believe in providing firearms to responsible people who understand the importance of the 2nd Amendment, and the responsibility we have to protect it.  We are not interested in supplying firearms to those in society who do not have the morals, maturity, and character to be responsible gun owners.  It is our right to refuse to sell firearms to any person. We are interested in arming responsible citizens so that they can defend themselves against the criminal element, not arming the criminal element of society.

Local purchase information:
All federal and state laws apply. Buyer must complete ATF form 4473 and pass a standard background check in person. 6.5% Ohio sales tax will be collected from Ohio buyer. Please be sure the information on your driver's license is correct so that we can accept that for required identification purposes. 3.5% credit card processing fees apply; cash and check price is what is listed.

Out of State purchase information:
We will complete out of state sales by transferring the gun to your local FFL holder who will then complete the paperwork and background check. Shipping is normally $30, which covers packaging, shipping costs, tracking numbers, and insurance to the lower 48 states. Know your state gun laws before buying as there are no returns on this item. 3.5% credit card processing fees apply, money order/certified check price is what is listed.

Warranty and Return information:
If there is a manufacturing defect, the repair will be handled by the manufacturer's warranty or through our distributor's warranty. 

Contact us:
Please contact David Greer with Free Republic Firearms at REDACTED or by phone at REDACTED with any questions. We are located in Massillon, Ohio. To get updates of our new arrivals, "like" our Facebook page, and visit www.freerepublicfirearms.com for more information. If you contact us via email, please include your name and phone number to eliminate spammers and to ensure we can contact you. Occasionally we have problems with messages from hidden email addresses that are sent through gun listing/auction sites. Our reply emails are being returned as undeliverable, so if we don't respond to your email, please make sure we have another way to contact you.  We do not hold firearms, magazines, and accessories, because people do not always follow through with the purchase. Items are sold on a first come; first serve basis.

Trades:
We will consider trades from local, in-person buyers, but we cannot give a value on a gun unless we see it in person. Most of our firearms are new, and we are very selective about what used firearms we sell.   Please realize will cannot pay full retail for your firearm. We are a business, and there has to be room for us to make a small amount when we resell the firearm.  Let us know what you have to trade, and we will let you know if it is something we need.  If you are an out of state buyer, we will not consider a trade. 

Extra information:
To all the spammers and criminals that can't legally buy guns, don't contact us asking to meet in a parking lot to complete a cash sale, or to trade a stolen laptop or other electronics for our guns. You shouldn't have guns, and we're definitely not going to help you get one.  To those who are under the legal age to buy firearms or handguns, we understand your desire to have a gun, but we will not break the law to sell you one, so please don't ask.
